# AI-Enabled Real-Time Voice Transcription & Reflexive Question Generator

## Project Overview

This project is an AI-powered healthcare consultation assistant built using Flask, Hugging Face Transformers, OpenAI Whisper, and NLP-based conversational AI modules.

The system simulates a doctor-patient interaction where:

- The system asks predefined medical questions
- The patient responds using voice
- Speech is converted into text in real time
- AI analyzes patient responses
- Context-aware reflexive follow-up questions are generated
- A final medical summary is produced automatically



The application supports:
- Real-time speech-to-text
- Dynamic AI-generated follow-up questions
- Medical consultation flow management
- AI-generated consultation summaries
- OCR-based image text extraction
- Text-to-speech doctor responses

---
## Project Screenshot

![Homepage](assets/homepage.png)
# Core Features

## 1. Real-Time Voice Transcription
Uses OpenAI Whisper model to:
- Capture microphone audio
- Detect language automatically
- Convert speech into text

Supported Languages:
- English
- Hindi

---

## 2. AI Reflexive Question Generation
Uses Microsoft Phi-2 transformer model to:
- Analyze patient responses
- Generate medically relevant follow-up questions
- Maintain contextual conversation flow

Example:
Doctor: Do you smoke?
Patient: Yes occasionally.

AI Follow-Up:
"How many cigarettes do you smoke per day?"

---

## 3. Medical Consultation Flow
The consultation follows:
- Structured medical script
- Dynamic AI-generated reflexive questions
- Conversation history tracking

---

## 4. AI Medical Summary Generation
Uses FLAN-T5 model by Google to:
- Analyze complete consultation transcript
- Generate concise medical summaries
- Highlight important medical risks

---

## 5. OCR Image Upload Support
Users can upload:
- Medical reports
- Prescriptions
- Lab results

The system:
- Extracts text using OCR (Tesseract)
- Generates AI summaries from extracted text

---

## 6. Text-to-Speech Support
Doctor questions are converted into speech using gTTS.

This allows:
- Audio-based interaction
- Better accessibility
- Natural conversational experience

---

